  <data name="ConsequencesRevocation" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Consequences of the revocation</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ConsequencesRevocation1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>If you cancel this contract, we will reimburse all payments received from you, including delivery costs for standard delivery, without undue delay and at the latest within 14 days from the day we receive your cancellation notice. This excludes any additional costs incurred due to a delivery method other than the cheapest standard delivery option.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ConsequencesRevocation2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The refund will be issued using the same payment method you used for the original order, unless otherwise agreed.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReturnGoods" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Return of goods</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReturnGoods1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>If you cancel the contract, please return the goods to us immediately and no later than 14 days after receipt. The customer bears the return shipping costs, to the extent permitted by law.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="RightOfWithdrawall" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>RightOfWithdrawal</value>
  </data>
  <data name="RightOfWithdrawalText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>To exercise your right of withdrawal, you must inform us</value>
  </data>
  <data name="RightOfWithdrawalText1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>inform us of your decision to cancel the order by means of a clear statement (e.g. by email, Whatsapp or letter).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="RightsConsumer" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Your legal rights as a consumer</value>
  </data>
  <data name="RightsConsumer1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Consumers have the right to withdraw from an online order within fourteen (14) days without giving any reason, unless there is a legal exclusion.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="RightsConsumer2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The cancellation period is 14 days from the day on which you or a third party named by you, who is not the carrier, have taken possession of the ordered goods.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Special instructions for food</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>1- Sealed food products:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The right of withdrawal does not apply to food products that were delivered sealed if the seal has been broken after delivery. This is because these products are unsuitable for return for reasons of health protection or hygiene (§ 312g para. 2 no. 3 BGB).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>2. Perishable foods:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>There is also no right of withdrawal for food products that spoil quickly or whose best-before date would soon be exceeded.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>3. Returns:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SpecialInstructionsFood6" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Returns of opened food products will not be refunded. In exceptional cases.</value>
